    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Mark is designing an eye-catching way to attract customers to visit his shop. Your goal is to display a word to promote his shop based on his idea:<br><br>1. break word into syllables<br>2. add <strong>space</strong><const>/</const><strong>space</strong> between syllables<br>3. add <strong>space</strong><const>!</const> at the end<br><br>A <const>vowel</const> is any of the letters <const>A</const>, <const>E</const>, <const>I</const>, <const>O</const> and <const>U</const>.<br><br>A word is broken into syllables by grouping <strong>consecutive vowels</strong>, i.e. each syllable contains 1 group of consecutive vowels.<br><br>If there is no vowel, the whole word is a syllable.<br><br>Treatment of consonants between vowels:<br>1. <const>1</const> consonant: it belongs to the second syllable.<br>2. <const>&gt;1</const> consonants: the first consonant belongs to the first syllable, the other consonants belong to the second syllable.<br><br>To illustrate: (c denotes a consonant, and V denotes a vowel)<br><br><pre style=\"font-family: monospace\">cccVcVVccVVVccc</pre><br>There are 3 groups of consecutive vowels, so the word is broken into 3 syllables, like this:<br><br><pre style=\"font-family: monospace\">cccV / cVVc / cVVVccc</pre></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> A string <var>word</var></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> A string, which is <var>word</var> formatted based on Mark's idea</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">3 &le; length of <var>word</var> &le; 15<br><var>word</var> contains uppercase letters only</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">SUPERB</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">SU / PERB !</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
